article.description: — Kalob Ledoux had 24 points as Louisiana Tech defeated Southeastern Louisiana 78-69 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Ledoux carries Louisiana Tech over SE Louisiana 78-69
article.linkText: Ledoux carries Louisiana Tech over SE Louisiana 78-69
article.story: RUSTON, La. -- — Kalob Ledoux had 24 points as Louisiana Tech defeated Southeastern Louisiana 78-69 on Wednesday night. Amorie Archibald had 16 points for Louisiana Tech (4-1), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. Isaiah Crawford added 10 points and JaColby Pemberton had seven rebounds. Pape Diop had 15 points and eight rebounds for the Lions (1-5). Gus Okafor added 14 points. Keon Clergeot had six rebounds, seven turnovers and three assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
